===Etymology===
From the inventor of the process John Mercer of Great Harwood, Lancashire, in the middle of the 19th century.

===Alternative forms===
* (UK) [[mercerise]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|mercerizes|mercerizing|mercerized|mercerized}}

# To treat [[cotton]] fabric with [[sodium hydroxide]] to make it more [[lustrous]] and accepting of dyes.

